,"modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"V\tVoyage mostly as expected. Even with an additional disport, nil demurrage incurred as everything moved fairly quickly. \n-\tThe addition of Wilhelmshaven as a disport increases freight by $200k, port costs by $65k, and time by about 2 days.\n-\tRotterdam port costs and differential decrease by abt $50k with only part cargo discharge\n-\tVessel was given approval to tender NOR one day before laycan in Corpus Christi. \n-\tCorpus Christi Port costs $30k less than estimated\n-\tHFO supply continued to be a problem in the USG and resulted in us having to deviate to Bolivar after loading, losing just under a day.\n-\tCharterers elected to speed vessel up on laden passage, essentially making up time lost in Bolivar while paying us for the additional bunkers ($12k).\n-\tVessel continues to have great consumption with $130k in bunker savings"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-14T17:24:14.773","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TC Increase $1.2k with updated estimated Rotterdam harbor dues"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-13T14:58:04.007","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TC Increase $1.5k with lower than estimated bunker consumption"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-06T18:12:14.5","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TC Increase $1.5k with lower than estimated bunker consumption"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-29T16:20:54.377","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Increase with routing outside of ECA"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-22T14:54:15.293","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TCE Increase $1.5kpd with less time in GOLA for bunkers and consumption less than estimated"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}